        "body": "The four numbers next to each exercise (e.g. 3-1-1-0) describe tempo in seconds: eccentric (lowering) — pause at the bottom — concentric (lifting) — rest at the top. A 3-1-1-0 back squat means 3 seconds down, 1 second pause at the bottom, 1 second up, no rest at the top. Controlling tempo is how you build real tissue capacity — rushing reps to hit the numbers defeats the whole purpose of the session."
